Welcome to **Toum**, the app that helps you reconnect after one encounter and organize hangouts with real friends. By creating an account or using Toum, you agree to the following Terms of Use:

---

## 1. Acceptance of Terms

By signing up or using Toum, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agree to these Terms of Use and our [Privacy Policy](https://github.com/pepiteman/toum-app/blob/main/privacy-policy.md).  
If you do not agree, you may not use the app.

---

## 2. Eligibility

- You must be at least 13 years old to use Toum.  
- If you are under the age of majority in your country, you must have parental permission.  

---

## 3. User Content

Toum lets you:  
- Create and join hangouts with your friends.  
- Add close friends and chat with them.  
- Write short descriptions for hangouts.  
- Exchange text messages in chat.  

At this time, you cannot share photos, videos, or other media through Toum.  

You are fully responsible for the text you post in hangout descriptions or chat messages.  

You agree **not** to use Toum to share:  
- Nudity, sexual content, or pornography.  
- Violence, threats, or hate speech.  
- Harassment, bullying, or abusive behavior.  
- Spam, scams, or illegal activity.  

We may remove any hangout, description, or message and suspend accounts that violate these rules.

---

## 4. Safety & Reporting

Toum has **no tolerance** for objectionable content or abusive users.  
- You can **block** other users.  
- You can **report** messages, hangouts, or users if you believe they violate these Terms.  
- Reports are reviewed within **24 hours**, and content or users in violation will be removed.  

